0029|- [HelpText]
0030|*Various special keys and key combinations:
0032|* ESC activates the operation on the current line.
0033|* ENTER moves the cursor to the start of the next line.
0034|* END moves the cursor to the end of the line.
0035|* CTRL-END erases the line from the current position to the right.
0036|*      If shadow characters occur, the shadows are erased first.
0037|* (RIGHT) moves the cursor one step to the right.
0038|* (LEFT) moves the cursor one step to the left.
0039|* (UP) moves the cursor one step upwards.
0040|* (DOWN) moves the cursor one step downwards.
0042|* HOME moves cursor primarily to the first column, then to the first
0043|*      line and finally to the first position in the edit field.
0045|* TAB moves the cursor to the next tab position which is defined
0046|*      by the T characters on the first edit line having a 'T' in
0047|*      its control column. If no T line is found, columns 11,21,31,41,...
0048|*      are the default tab positions. After TAB is pressed, numbers to
0049|*      be typed will be correctly aligned to form straight columns.
