0240|*ALT-F2:WORDS
0241|*  WORDS initiates the definition of a sequence of words (sentence)
0242|*      either to be moved to another place or deleted.
0243|*      Prompts for alternative actions will appear on the bottom line.
0244|*      The sequence of words is defined by indicating the first letter
0245|*      of the first word by WORDS and the last letter of the last word
0246|*      by WORDS again.
0247|*      Thereafter the sequence is deleted by CTRL-END or moved to another
0248|*      place indicated by the cursor by WORDS. In the latter case the
0249|*      cursor should usually point to a space between two words.
0250|*      To preserve the sequence in its original position, enter insert
0251|*      mode before pressing WORDS. In any case, the sequence is saved
0252|*      in a special file and it can be copied to any place later
0253|*      by pressing WORDS in that place 4 times.
0254|*                                               (continued on next page)
0256|*  WORDS (continued)
0257|*      The text chapters are also automatically adjusted if a model
0258|*      for a suitable TRIM operation is given by a line of the form
0259|*          autotrim=TRIM3 72
0260|- shadow %: [LINK(q0b_10.html)] [/LINK]
0261|*      in the SURVO.APU file (See APU?).
