0289|- [HelpText]
0290|*ALT-F4:BLOCK
0291|*  BLOCK initiates a sequence of key strokes for defining a rectangular
0292|*      block in the current edit field. Prompts for alternative actions
0293|*      will appear on the bottom line. A block is defined by indicating
0294|*      its two opposite corners (by BLOCK) and it can then be copied
0295|*      to various places (by BLOCK) and/or it can be erased (by CTRL-END).
0296|*      To interrupt these actions after BLOCK has pressed, press DELETE.
0297|*      If the insert mode is not on, the blocks will overwrite existing
0298|*      parts of the edit field.
0299|*      If the insert mode is on, new lines will be automatically inserted
0300|*      below the current line and the block is copied to these lines.
0301|- shadow %: [LINK(q06_06.html)] [/LINK]
0302|*      (See also WORDS?)
S   |                 %%%%%
0303|*      When a block defined by the BLOCK (alt-F4) key has been moved or
0304|*      erased at least once, it is also saved in a temporary file
0305|*      <Survo>\TMP\SURVO.BLO .
S   |       <     >
0306|*      The latest block (although not anymore highlighted in the edit field)
0307|*      can then be copied to the current edit field simply by pressing
0308|*      the BLOCK key four times.
0310|- [New]
0311|- shadow %: [LINK(q0c_17.html)] [/LINK]
