0319|- [HelpText]
0320|*ALT-F5:SEARCH
0321|*  SEARCH initiates a search in the edit field. The user is
0322|*      prompted to enter the characters of the search string one after
0323|*      another and the first occurrence of the string is shown
0324|*      immediately in each stage. The process is interrupted until the
0325|*      given string is not found anymore or by pressing ENTER.
0326|*      During the search, other cases are found by pressing ESC.
0327|- shadow %: [LINK(q05_13.html)] [/LINK]
0328|*      (See also FIND?)
S   |                 %%%%
0329|- [New]
0330|*      F2 | works similarly but limits the search for words starting
0331|*      from the first column in the edit field.
0332|- [/New]
0333|*F2 ALT-F5:
0334|*      works as ALT-F5 but the search goes backwards in the edit field.
0335|*      (See also -FIND?)
0337|*      A search can be started from a ready-typed keyword touched
0338|*      by the cursor. Then after ALT-F5 or F2 ALT-F5 press ALT-F5 again.
0339|*      A search can also be started from the keyword used in the previous
0340|*      search by pressing F5 after ALT-F5 or F2 ALT-F5.
0341|*      HOME takes to the beginning/end of the edit field, depending on
0342|*      the direction of the search.
