0387|*Function keys F11 and F12 are available as shortcut keys for
0388|*activation of important sucros selected by the user.
0389|*The functions (names of sucros) are given by `sucro_key' lines
0390|*in the SURVO.APU file as follows:
0391|*                                        alternative key
0392|*  sucro_key1=<sucro for F11>            Ctrl-A
S   |              <             >
0393|*  sucro_key2=<sucro for F12>            Ctrl-B
S   |              <             >
0394|*  sucro_key3=<sucro for shift-F11>
S   |              <                   >
0395|*  sucro_key4=<sucro for shift-F12>      Ctrl-D
S   |              <                   >
0396|*  sucro_key5=<sucro for ctrl-F11>       Ctrl-E
S   |              <                  >
0397|*  sucro_key6=<sucro for ctrl-F12>       Ctrl-F
S   |              <                  >
0398|*  sucro_key7=<sucro for alt-F11>        Ctrl-G
S   |              <                 >
0399|*  sucro_key8=<sucro for alt-F12>
S   |              <                 >
0401|*For example, one possible selection could be:
0402|*  sucro_key1=V            / Show the current menu of Survo jobs
0403|*  sucro_key2=SURVO-START  / Show the main menu of Survo
0404|*  sucro_key3=SURVO-SETUP  / Show the menu of system parameters setting
0405|*The easiest way to see the current list of sucro keys and to maintain it
0406|*is to use the /SURVO-SETUP sucro (which also should have a place
0407|*in that list; see the preceding example).
